&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Medical Directorate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pre-Registration Trainee Pharmacy Technician(Fixed Term Temporary apprenticeship)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Government Apprenticeship Scheme&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:Pharmacy Department&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Michael Carlisle Centre, Sheffield&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5 hours per week&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ost Ref: 457-20-029-MD&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you have a keen interest in maths and science and wish to undertake further studies?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like the opportunity to work toward the level 3 Diplomas in Pharmacy and register as a Pharmacy Technician?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have answered yes to any of these questions you may be interested in a two-year apprenticeship style training scheme which is available at Sheffield Health and Social Care NHS Trust, based at the Michael Carlisle Centre in Sheffield.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will attend Sheffield College on a day release basis to undertake a BTEC Level 3 Diploma in Pharmaceutical Science, whilst training in the workplace (NHS Hospital) 4 days per week to obtain and prove competence in the Level 3 NVQ Diploma in Pharmacy Service Skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The opportunity offers 2 years comprehensive training in all aspects of pharmacy services on a rotational basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individuals will need to be highly organised and motivated and be capable of meeting multiple deadlines. We will expect applicants to have an understanding of the role of a Pharmacy Technician (or have previous experience of working in a pharmacy).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Students who successfully complete the 2-year course and associated study will be eligible to register as a Pharmacy Technician with the General Pharmaceutical Council (GPhC)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To be eligible for consideration for a Pre-Registration Trainee Pharmacy Technician interview, you MUST meet all essential criteria and have a MINIMUM of:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5 GCSEs at grade C or above (or equivalent), including English Language, Maths and 2 Sciences (or dual award)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants MUST have the required minimum qualifications and will be asked to bring original certificates to interview (or predicted grades for school leavers, on official letter headed school/college paper).&lt;/p&gt;
